article_title: Covered California has insured 11,000 in San Luis Obispo County
article_text:
Bus tour stops in Templeton to promote health insurance exchange as open enrollment period opens

Since exchange began, county’s uninsured as fallen from 16 percent to 10 percent

State officials emphasize that subsidies are available to help pay monthly premiums

article_metadata.news-keywords: Covered California, Lee, Borenstein, ACA, Affordable Care Act, health insurance, premiums, subsidies
article_metadata.description: About 11,000 people in San Luis Obispo County, primarily from the North and South counties, are enrolled today in individual health insurance policies through Covered California, County Health Officer Dr. Penny Borenstein said Wednesday.
